<h1 id="vendor-payment-overview" sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="26">Vendor payment overview</h1>

[!include[banner](../../includes/banner.md)]
<p sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="30">This task guide will walk you through various methods used to create vendor payments, including how to use a payment proposal or manually entering a one-off payment. This procedure uses the USMF demo company.</p>
<ol sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="32">
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="32">Go to <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="32">Navigation pane &gt; Modules &gt; Accounts payable &gt; Payments &gt; Payment journal</strong>.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="33">Click <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="33">New</strong>.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="34">Select the payment journal in which to save the vendor payments.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="35">Select the journal or manually enter it.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="36">Click <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="36">Lines</strong>.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="37">On <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="37">Ation pane</strong>, click <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="37">Payment proposal</strong>.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="38">Click <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="38">Create payment proposal</strong>. The payment proposal is a query used to select invoices for payment. You can edit the list of invoices to pay before creating or generating the vendor payments.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="39">Select invoices for payment by due date, cash discount, or both.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="40">Enter the date for comparing to the due date or cash discount.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="41">Optional: Enter a payment date used for all payments. The date entered here will be the payment date for all payments created, regardless of the due date or cash discount date.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="42">Optional: Enter a minimum payment date which may be used as the payment date. The minimum payment date will be the earliest date used when creating payments. For example, if an invoice has a due date after the minimum payment date, the due date will become the payment date instead of the minimum payment date in order to pay the invoice on the latest possible date.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="43">Enter additional query restrictions under <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="43">Records to include</strong> section. The filter is often used to restrict the invoices selected for payment by vendor group or method of payment. For example, you may add a filter to only pay invoices by check in this pay run.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="44">Enter additional query restriction or payment defaults. The additional parameters can be used to define the payment currency or to enable centralized payments for this pay run.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="45">Click <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="45">OK</strong>. After clicking <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="45">OK</strong>, the results of the query will appear. If you don't want to preview the list of invoices selected to pay, you can go back to the <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="45">Parameters</strong> fast tab and change the setting <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="45">Create payments without invoice preview</strong> to &quot;Yes&quot;.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="46">Choose the <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="46">Show payment overview</strong> button to view the payments that will be created for the vendor on the invoice selected.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="47">Choose the <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="47">Hide payment overview</strong> button to hide the payments.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="48">Click <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="48">Create payments</strong>. Before choosing <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="48">Create payments</strong>, you can right click on the grid and export the list of invoices to Excel. The <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="48">Create payments</strong> button will create the vendor payments in the payment journal.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="49">Scan your payments and make sure the method of payment is defined for all payments. If you generate the payments, such as printing a check or creating an electronic payment, the method of payment must be defined. The method of payment will also default the bank account from the payment will be made.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="50">Click <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="50">New</strong> to create a one-off payment. A one-off payment can be added to a payment journal at any time prior to posting. This is done by clicking the <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="50">New</strong> button and adding the payment information manually, rather than using the <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="50">Payment proposal</strong>.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="51">Select the vendor to whom the payment will be made.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="52">If an invoice exists to pay, select <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="52">Settle transactions</strong> to select the invoice for payment. If this is a prepayment, this step is optional. You can create the payment without selecting any invoice.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="53">Mark any invoices that will be paid. If you use the <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="53">Settle transactions</strong> to select the invoices for payment, the payment amount will automatically be calculated based on what invoices you mark for payment, and what amount you enter in the <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="53">Amount to settle</strong>.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="54">Click <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="54">OK</strong>.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="55">If you want to delete a payment, mark the row.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="56">Click <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="56">Delete</strong>. Deleting a payment will only delete the payment. Any invoices marked for payment will still be available to be paid by another payment.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="57">Click <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="57">Yes</strong>.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="58">Choose <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="58">Generate payment</strong> to print checks or create the electronic payment file.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="59">Select the method of payment that you want to generate. The payment journal can contain payments for both Checks and electronic payments, but you can only generate one payment type at a time.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="60">Select the bank account from which to generate the payments.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="61">Click <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="61">OK</strong>. Payments will only be generated for payments that match the <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="61">Method of payment</strong> and <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="61">Bank account</strong> you selected.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="62">If you are generating <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="62">Checks</strong>, choose <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="62">Document</strong> to ensure the correct print destination for the checks.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="63">Click <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="63">OK</strong>.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="64">Click <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="64">OK</strong> to generate the payments.</li>
<li sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="65">Click <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/cash-bank-management/tasks/vendor-payment-overview.md" sourcestartlinenumber="65">Post</strong> if all the payments are approved and generated.</li>
</ol>
